Ouma said the new curriculum will allow the children to compete without subjecting them to national examinations, which education experts have described as &ldquo;death sentence for learners who fail".He said in the new curriculum, which is expected to be fully rolled out by the year 2021, has focused on content, skills and competency for the learners.The KICD will train teachers in phases about the new curriculum starting August this year.Ouma said other countries of the world have changed their education system, therefore Kenya cannot lag behind as the world moves on.